 font-size:11pt">and connected to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the dominant ideas of rationality and disinterested inquiry </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">science ostensibly stands</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">pivotal Greenfield report </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(2002)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> commissioned by the government </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and subsequent papers such as that of Kirkup et al (2010) only touch on the underlying sexism that exists in sc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ience</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our work foregrounds it. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 9pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We believe that subtle and not-so-subtle </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sex</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ism disadvantages women and exacerbates attrition rates. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In terms of the proportions of women reaching senior positions, the evidence is clear. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In the major employer of healthcare scientists in the UK where VB was employed, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">many </span><span style="font-family:'Tim