ust happened to be a man’. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">After much debate, a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">greement was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">subsequently </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ga</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ined </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to improve </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the practices on recruitment </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ensure a more even representation on future panels</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in spite of this agreement, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">owever</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> another all-male recruitment panel was convened within two months and another man </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">appointed. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The assumption seemed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to be that a mix of gender and ethnic backgrounds on appointment panels was unnecessary.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 9pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span styl