>adequately </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to challenge decisions made. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 9pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">One example was the closure of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on-site nursery because it was said that it was a financial burden to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">organization</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Although an equality imp</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">act assessment was carried out by senior managers, the benefits to working mothers (and fathers) were not considered of great enough importance to keep the nursery open. Despite active opposition from staff </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">clearly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">showing how people were to be disadvantag</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the executive group considered that closure of the nursery was the ‘safest decision based on the financial circumstances’.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 9pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Another example was that reduced cover for maternity leave was used as a way of saving money. In some cases, staff at a lower gra</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">de were app